The paper discusses techniques for solving the AllSAT problem, which is a variant of propositional satisfiability. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), logic in computer science (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
